The paper deals with Tverberg's theorem, which is a fundamental result in discrete geometry. The paper also discusses algorithmic aspects and provides a concrete application in the plane. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves combinatorial aspects, so cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a likely category. The paper discusses generalizations and algorithmic aspects, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.MG (Mathematical Software). Finally, the paper involves numerical computations, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
